('Swimming Open Water Sighting Drill',
 'neck', array['shoulder','core','hip_flexors'], array['neck','shoulder','core'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['open_water','wetsuit'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Open water swimming skill for triathlon or OWS racing. Sighting technique: every 8-10 strokes, lift head briefly to see forward while body stays horizontal. Practice: (1) Crocodile sighting: eyes barely above water, 2-stroke sight then 2-stroke back to bilateral rhythm. (2) Buoy navigation drill: swim to far buoy sighting every 8 strokes. (3) Drafting practice: swim directly behind another swimmer 1-2m back.',
 'Full head lift breaking body line; sighting too frequently increasing drag; losing stroke rhythm after sighting; not returning to bilateral breathing after sight.',
 'open_water_skill', array['2 eyes at water level — not full head lift','Breathe on the next stroke after sighting','Know your bearing before you enter the water','Draft on the feet of the swimmer ahead — free speed'],
 array['Full open water race simulation','Surf conditions open water practice','Open water navigation sprint'],
 array['Pool sighting drill practice','Stationary head position practice','Calm lake swimming with frequent sighting'],
 array['swimming','open_water','sighting','triathlon','navigation','OWS'], array[],
 'mixed', 'sagittal', false, 3, null, null, 30, true),

('Swimming Lactate Threshold Training',
 'cardiovascular', array['lats','core','glutes'], array['cardiovascular','lats','core'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['pool','pace_clock'], 'advanced', false,
 'T-pace (threshold pace) training for competitive swimmers. T-pace = 1000m time trial pace minus 2 seconds per 100m. Main set: 5-8x400m at T-pace with 30s rest. Alternate: 20x100m with 10s rest at T-pace. Track HR: should reach 85-90% of max by rep 3-4 and stay there. Monthly T-pace test to track adaptation.',
 'Going too fast at start of T-pace set (race pace mentality); taking more rest than prescribed; not swimming in streamline position maintaining technique under fatigue; skipping T-pace testing so improvement is unmeasured.',
 'aerobic_capacity', array['T-pace is uncomfortable but sustainable','Maintain stroke count per length — efficiency under fatigue','Your threshold pace is earned through consistent training','10s rest in the 100s set is not recovery — keep the engine running'],
 array['Over-distance lactate threshold (800m-1200m reps)','T-pace set with descending rest','Race season threshold maintenance sets'],
