 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['resistance_bands','foam_roller'], 'beginner', false,
 'Swimmer impingement prevention protocol (evidence-based). (1) Serratus anterior activation: wall push-up with plus (protract at top) 3x15. (2) Lower trap activation: prone Y-raise with external rotation 3x12. (3) Posterior capsule stretch: sleeper stretch 3x30s each. (4) Band external rotation: 90/90 position 3x15. (5) Pec minor stretch against wall 3x30s. (6) Foam roller thoracic extension 2x60s.',
 'Skipping serratus exercises (scapular dyskinesis is primary impingement cause); not addressing thoracic stiffness; performing overhead exercises before adequate prep; ignoring pec minor tightness.',
