('Swimming Race Warm-Up Protocol',
 'cardiovascular', array['shoulder','core','lats'], array['cardiovascular','shoulder','core'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['pool','resistance_bands'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Pre-race warm-up (90 min before start, 45 minutes in pool). Structure: (1) 400m easy free, breathing every 3. (2) 4x50m build (easy/moderate/fast/very fast). (3) Stroke drill set 4x50m. (4) 4x25m at race pace. (5) 100m easy cool-down. (6) Exit pool: resistance band activation 5 min for shoulder and lats. (7) Re-enter: 2x15m race pace for CNS activation. End 20 min before race.',
 'Warming up too long and arriving fatigued; not including race-pace efforts in warm-up (CNS not activated); cooling down too much after warm-up then waiting; poor race-day routine inconsistency.',
 'race_prep', array['Your warm-up should finish with race-pace efforts','End in the water 20 minutes before your race','Build intensity progressively — don''t sprint in your warm-up','Consistent race day routine: remove variables'],
 array['Full race simulation warm-up protocol','Competition taper warm-up adjustment','Multi-event day warm-up management'],
 array['Basic 200m easy warm-up','In-place band warm-up only','Stretching-only pre-race warm-up'],
