 'mixed', 'sagittal', false, 1, null, null, null, true),

('Swimming Hypoxic Training Protocol',
 'cardiovascular', array['diaphragm','core','lats'], array['cardiovascular','diaphragm','core'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['pool'], 'advanced', false,
 'Breath-hold and hypoxic training to improve CO2 tolerance and breathing economy. Session: (1) Static breath hold in water (face down): 6x15-20s with 30s rest — builds comfort, not endurance. (2) Hypoxic set: 6x50m breathing every 7 strokes. (3) Underwater swims: 3x12m underwater kick-only after push-off. (4) Recovery: bilateral breathing 200m after any hypoxic set. Always swim with partner for safety.',
 'Performing static breath holds alone without a partner — safety risk; extending breath holds beyond personal limit; hyperventilating before breath holds (increases blackout risk); forgetting to signal partner.',
 'hypoxic_training', array['NEVER do breath hold swimming alone','Signal your partner before each hold','Hyperventilation before hold INCREASES blackout risk — never do it','If you feel light-headed, stop immediately'],
 array['Progressive hypoxic distance increase','Hypoxic sets at race pace','CO2 tolerance ladder set'],
 array['Easy bilateral breathing pattern','Breathing every 2 strokes only','Comfortable breathing pattern swimming'],
