('Cycling Cadence Drill (High RPM)',
 'quads', array['glutes','hamstrings','calves'], array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','trainer','cadence_sensor'], 'intermediate', false,
 'High cadence neuromuscular training. Warm up 10 min. Main set: 6x3 minutes at 100-110 RPM in a light gear maintaining smooth circles (not bouncing). Rest 2 min easy between. Then: 4x1 min @ 120 RPM (leg speed drill). Cool down. Track: is your hips rocking? If yes, lower cadence until smooth. Goal: develop efficient circular pedalling.',
 'Hip rocking side to side (saddle too low or cadence too high for current ability); bouncing in saddle; overly heavy breathing suggesting cadence is too high — drop back 10 RPM; neglecting smooth circles.',
