('Cycling VO2max Interval Training',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','power_meter','trainer'], 'advanced', true,
 'Classic 4x8 minute VO2max intervals. Warm up 15 min with 3x30s openers. Main set: 4 reps of 8 minutes at 106-120% FTP with 4 minutes easy recovery between. These should be very hard but sustainable. Cool down 10 minutes easy. Perceived effort: 8-9/10 for last 2 minutes. Power should hold ± 5% across all 4 reps.',
 'Starting rep 1 too hard and dying on rep 3-4; not taking full recovery between reps; cadence too low increasing muscular fatigue over aerobic; choosing too high a target resulting in failure.',
