('Cycling Sweet Spot Training',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','power_meter','trainer'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Sweet spot (88-93% FTP) is the highest training ROI zone. Session: 2x20 minutes @ 88-93% FTP with 5-minute easy spin between. Or: 3x15 minutes for beginners. Steady-state power — no surges, no drifting below zone. Monitor: cadence 85-95 RPM, breathing conversational-to-hard but sustainable. Weekly volume build: +5-10% per week.',
 'Power drifting below zone turning session into tempo; taking too many rest breaks within reps; choosing too high FTP target making it VO2max instead of sweet spot; neglecting cadence efficiency.',
 'threshold_endurance', array['Sweet spot: hard enough to matter, soft enough to recover','Find the power you can hold and hold it — no drifting','Breathe through your nose at the start of each rep','Log every session: track your trend'],
