('Cycling Single-Leg Pedalling Drill',
 'quads', array['hip_flexors','glutes','calves'], array['quads','hip_flexors','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','trainer'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Unilateral pedalling for stroke efficiency. Trainer with one foot clipped in and unclip other foot (or rest on trainer). 30 seconds single-leg, 30 seconds both legs, 30 seconds other single-leg. Repeat 6 times. Focus: pulling up on backstroke, scraping back at bottom, pushing over the top. Listen for dead spots — clunking at 6 o''clock position.',
 'Pushing only downward (dead spot at bottom and top of stroke); trying to maintain normal cadence (single-leg will naturally be lower); over-pulling up leading to cramp.',
