('Cycling Zone 2 Aerobic Base Training',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','heart_rate_monitor'], 'beginner', true,
 'Low-intensity aerobic base building. Target: Zone 2 HR (65-75% max HR, or 56-75% FTP). Ride for 60-120 minutes at steady pace. Nasal breathing test: if you can''t breathe through your nose, you''re too hard. Conversation test: can speak full sentences. This is mitochondrial development work. Weekly volume: 3-4 zone 2 sessions for base building.',
 'Riding too hard — creeping into zone 3 (the grey zone); cutting sessions short; not having patience with slow-seeming progress; mixing intervals into zone 2 ride.',
 'aerobic_base', array['If you can''t breathe through your nose — slow down','Zone 2 is where aerobic engines are built','Boring? Good. Bore yourself to fitness','Consistent months of zone 2 beats irregular hard sessions'],
