 'Basic bike fit protocol for coaches to assess clients. (1) Saddle height: heel on pedal at 6 o''clock = slight bend at knee. Clipped in: 25-35° knee flexion at bottom. (2) Saddle fore-aft: knee over pedal spindle at 3 o''clock. (3) Handlebar reach: slight elbow bend, relaxed shoulders. (4) Cleat position: ball of foot over spindle center. Video assessment from side and front.',
 'Saddle too high causing hip rocking; saddle too far back causing loss of power; handlebar too far causing lower back strain; cleat misaligned causing knee tracking issues.',
