('Cycling Climbing Strength Intervals',
 'glutes', array['quads','hamstrings','core'], array['glutes','quads','hamstrings'],
 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['bike','trainer'], 'advanced', true,
 'Neuromuscular climbing strength at low cadence. After warm-up: 6x5 minutes at 50-60 RPM seated on heavy resistance at 95-105% FTP. Full recovery 4 minutes between. This develops the muscular strength component of climbing — different from high cadence work. Keep torso still, push down powerfully through each pedal stroke.',
