('Cycling Over-Under Interval Training',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','power_meter','trainer'], 'advanced', true,
 'Cross FTP repeatedly to develop ability to respond to race attacks. Format: 2x12-minute blocks. Within each block: alternate 90s at 108% FTP (over) and 90s at 95% FTP (under) continuously. Rest 5 minutes between blocks. The over segments push lactate up; under segments clear lactate partially before next over. Total: 24 minutes of work.',
 'Over percentage too high causing early failure; under recovery too passive (coasting instead of 95%); not completing the full over phase; insufficient rest between main blocks.',
