('Cycling Descending Technique and Cornering',
 'core', array['quads','glutes','shoulder'], array['core','quads','shoulder'],
 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['bike','road'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Technical skills for safe and efficient descending. (1) Body position: weight low, bent elbows, hands on drops/brake hoods. (2) Vision: look through the corner to exit, not at hazard. (3) Braking: before the corner, not in it. (4) Pedal position: outside pedal down, weight in outside pedal. (5) Lean: lean the bike, not just your body. Practice: series of wide corners gradually tightening.',
 'Stiffening arms reducing bike handling; braking in the corner causing rear wheel skip; looking down instead of through corner; inside pedal down causing pedal strike.',
