('Cycling Peloton Riding and Drafting Skills',
 'cardiovascular', array['core','shoulder','quads'], array['cardiovascular','core','shoulder'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','group_ride'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Group riding and drafting skills. Aerodynamic benefit: riding 1m behind reduces energy cost by 30%. (1) Hold a wheel: steady distance 0.5-1m, absorb changes by feathering brakes not braking hard. (2) Rotational pace line: pull 30 seconds, soft pedal to back, recover, re-attach. (3) Echelon: crosswind formation at 45° to maximize draft. Practice on closed roads or with experienced group.',
