('Triathlon Brick Training (Bike + Run)',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['bike','run_shoes','GPS_watch'], 'intermediate', true,
 'The essential triathlon training method. Bike hard, then immediately run — simulates race physiology. Sprint tri brick: 30km bike at race effort immediately followed by 5km run at race pace. Olympic brick: 40km bike then 10km run. Key goal: train the legs to switch from cycling to running neuromuscular patterns. First km of run will feel terrible — this is normal.',
 'Taking too long between bike and run (defeats the purpose); running too fast on the brick run compounding fatigue; neglecting nutrition on the bike portion; making bricks too infrequent.',
 'race_specific', array['Get off the bike and start running immediately','Your legs will feel like lead for first km — push through','Maintain cadence: 180 steps/min off the bike','Race nutrition on the bike sets up the run'],
 array['Full Olympic distance simulation brick','Long course 140.6 brick simulation','Race-pace brick with T2 transition practice'],
 array['15 min bike + 5 min run intro brick','Stationary bike + treadmill brick for beginners','30 min easy bike then 15 min easy run'],
