('Triathlon Race Pacing Strategy (Olympic Distance)',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['GPS_watch','power_meter','heart_rate_monitor'], 'advanced', true,
 'Olympic distance (1.5km/40km/10km) pacing strategy. Swim: 90-92% max HR. Bike: 85-90% FTP (first 5km conservative, then build). Run: first 3km controlled, km 3-7 at goal race pace, final 3km all out. Fuel: gel at T1, gel at 20km on bike, gel at T2. Hydration: 500ml water per hour. Practice executing this plan in training simulations.',
