 'quads', array['calves','glutes','hip_flexors'], array['quads','calves','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'running', array['running_shoes','GPS_watch'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Triathlon-specific running technique for post-bike running. Key differences: (1) Shorten stride in first km — legs are in cycling pattern. (2) Increase cadence deliberately: target 180 spm. (3) Focus on forward lean from ankles. (4) Arm swing more vertical — recover from aerodynamic position. (5) Breathing pattern reset — deeper breaths for 2 minutes. Practice: 20-minute brick run following every ride.',
