('Triathlon Speed Work Run Intervals',
 'cardiovascular', array['quads','glutes','calves'], array['cardiovascular','quads','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'running', array['running_shoes','GPS_watch','track'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Triathlon-specific run speed work to improve 10km race pace. Session on fresh legs (NOT as a brick): 4x1km at 5km race pace with 90s recovery. Or: 10x400m at 5km race pace with 60s recovery. Warm up: 15 min easy + 4x100m strides. Cool down: 10 min easy. Weekly: one speed session per week during race-specific phase. This improves threshold speed which directly raises all slower paces.',
