('Golf Putting Mechanics and Mental Game',
 'shoulder', array['forearm','wrist','core'], array['shoulder','forearm','wrist'],
 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['putter','putting_green'], 'beginner', false,
 'Putting accounts for 40% of strokes. Mechanics: (1) Eyes directly over ball. (2) Shoulder-driven pendulum stroke (no wrist break). (3) Consistent tempo: count 1 (back) and 2 (through) — equal timing. (4) Head completely still through and after impact. Drills: (a) Gate drill: two tees slightly wider than putter face — must pass through clean. (b) 3-foot make 25 in a row. (c) Distance control: lag putting to circles.',
 'Wrist break in putting stroke (inconsistency); head moving at impact; poor grip pressure (too tight tightens wrists); no consistent pre-putt routine.',
 'technique_mental', array['Eyes over the ball: hold a ball under your chin, it should drop on the ball','Shoulder pendulum: feel your shoulders, not your hands','Consistent tempo is more important than technique details','Routine: same looks, same breath, same stroke — every putt'],
 array['Advanced putting statistics tracking','Pressure putting competition games','SAM puttlab or technology feedback'],
 array['Basic 3-foot putt fundamentals','Eyes-closed putting feel drill','Standing putt mechanics analysis'],
 array['golf','putting','mechanics','mental','technique','short_game'], array[],
 'isometric', 'sagittal', false, 3, null, null, 20, true),

('Golf Short Game Wedge Practice',
 'core', array['shoulder','forearm','wrist'], array['core','shoulder','forearm'],
 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['golf_wedges','golf_balls','short_game_area'], 'beginner', false,
 'Short game: pitch, chip, bunker. (1) Clock drill: 50m, 75m, 100m with each wedge (9-iron, PW, GW, SW) — 5 balls to each distance, 4 targets. (2) Chip and run: 10m landing spot chip to various pins from fringe. (3) Greenside bunker: same swing — open face, accelerate through, hit sand behind ball. (4) Flop shot practice: open face, full swing, land ball softly. Track: proximity to hole each session.',
 'Decelerating into chip (thin shots); poor bunker technique (hitting the ball not the sand); varying swing for different distances instead of varying club selection; no consistent contact spot tracking.',
 'short_game', array['Short game: landing spot not the hole — aim for where the ball will land','Bunker: hit the sand, not the ball — accelerate always','Chip: firm left wrist, don''t flick at impact','Proximity tracking: are your shots getting closer over time?'],
 array['Short game challenge game with partner','Creative lie practice in rough and uneven lies','Advanced flop shot practice from tight lies'],
 array['Basic chip from flat lie fringe','Putting from just off the green','Short iron full swings only'],
 array['golf','short_game','wedge','chipping','bunker','pitch'], array[],
 'mixed', 'multi', false, 4, 5, null, 30, true),

('Golf Injury Prevention Lower Back Protocol',
 'lower_back', array['core','glutes','hip_flexors'], array['lower_back','core','glutes'],
 'sport_specific', 'strength', array['bodyweight','foam_roller','resistance_bands'], 'beginner', false,
 'Lower back is the most common golf injury. Evidence-based prevention (McGill protocol adapted for golf): (1) McGill curl-up: tiny crunch maintaining lumbar curve 3x10s hold. (2) Bird dog: opposite arm and leg, spine neutral 3x10 each. (3) Side plank: 3x20-30s each side. (4) Hip flexor lunge stretch 3x45s. (5) Thoracic rotation (as above). (6) Cat-cow 3x10 gentle. Daily: 10 minutes before play.',
 'Flexing lumbar spine during golf swing (causes disc injury); not distinguishing hip hinge from back rounding; bypassing the stability work because it feels easy; not treating back pain early.',
 'injury_prevention', array['Neutral spine: there should be a curve in your lower back always','Hip hinge: bend at the hips NOT your lower back','Side plank: your life line for lower back health','McGill Big 3: 10 minutes daily prevents months of pain'],
 array['Full spinal health program for golfers','Return-to-golf back rehabilitation protocol','Load management and swing modification'],
 array['Passive lying down rest with knees bent','Gentle walking only','Cat-cow gentle spinal mobility only'],
 array['golf','lower_back','injury_prevention','McGill','rehabilitation','back_pain'], array['acute_disc_herniation','acute_lower_back_pain'],
