('Golf Competition Preparation Routine',
 'cardiovascular', array['core','shoulder','hip_flexors'], array['cardiovascular','core','shoulder'],
 'sport_specific', 'cardio', array['golf_clubs','course','range'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Competition week preparation for amateur and club golfers. Monday-Tuesday: practice full swing and short game (1h each). Wednesday: practice round on competition course (full round, note pin positions and course strategy). Thursday: rest and equipment check. Friday competition day: arrive 60 min before tee. Warm-up: physical (as above) + 20 balls on range + putting and chipping 20 min. Mental: game plan review.',
 'Over-practicing the day before competition (fatigue); making swing changes in competition week; not reviewing course strategy; neglecting pre-shot routine under competition pressure.',
 'competition_prep', array['Competition week: maintain don''t train','Practice round: strategy, not practice','Day before: short session to stay sharp, not work hard','Game plan: know your 14-club strategy before tee 1'],
 array['Full professional pre-tournament routine','Multi-round tournament preparation','Stroke play vs match play preparation differences'],
 array['Basic round warm-up only','Day-of competition warm-up minimal','Friendly round preparation relaxed approach'],
