 'Golf-specific fitness screening for coaches to assess client physical limitations. (1) Overhead deep squat: bilateral arm overhead, deep squat — assess mobility limitations. (2) Single-leg balance 30 seconds each side — note asymmetry. (3) Hip internal rotation measurement (seated): should be 45°+ each side. (4) Thoracic rotation: seated in chair, rotate both sides — note restriction. (5) Lat flexibility: overhead arm reach against wall. TPI 12-body region screen if certified.',
 'Assessing without context of golf swing faults; not connecting physical limitations to swing characteristics; over-pathologizing normal golf body types; not rescreening after 8-12 weeks of training.',
